data.name: Dark Alakazam
data.flavorText: Almost as if it were being controlled by something else, it never changes expressions, even in the middle of battle.

data.name: Dark Arbok
data.flavorText: Freezes its prey with its stare. If you should encounter one, remember not to look into its eyes.

data.name: Dark Blastoise
data.flavorText: An aggressive Pokémon that tackles anything it sees.

data.name: Dark Charizard
data.flavorText: Seemingly possessed, it spews fire like a volcano, trying to burn all it sees.

data.name: Dark Dragonite
data.flavorText: Sometimes called "The God of Destruction." Its wings are able to support it in spite of its massive weight.

data.name: Dark Dugtrio
data.flavorText: Digs large sinkholes in the ground and tries to trap its enemies in them.

data.name: Dark Golbat
data.flavorText: Sneaks up silently on its prey and attacks it from behind, sometimes killing it with one bite.

data.name: Dark Gyarados
data.flavorText: Normally found only in the deep ocean, it has recently been seen in shallow waters as well.

data.name: Dark Hypno
data.flavorText: Carries a pendulum with it always. Sometimes appears near less-traveled roads and schools at dusk.

data.name: Dark Machamp
data.flavorText: It is almost impossible to defend against a Machamp's four powerful arms.

data.name: Dark Magneton
data.flavorText: The number of incidents of hackers using Magnetons to damage computer systems is steadily increasing.

data.name: Dark Slowbro
data.flavorText: It loves nothing better than to be left alone, and so sometimes ends up being manipulated by unscrupulous people.

data.name: Dark Vileplume
data.flavorText: Perhaps because of their strong-smelling pollen, other Pokémon do not approach areas where Vileplumes live.

data.name: Dark Weezing
data.flavorText: Researchers have observed these Pokémon reproducing in industrial waste sites.

data.name: Dark Charmeleon
data.flavorText: Its tail is incredibly strong, able to lift up to 5 adult men.

data.name: Dark Dragonair
data.flavorText: As is fitting for a legendary Pokémon, it has many strange powers, including the ability to make rain or snow fall.

data.name: Dark Electrode
data.flavorText: Some researchers hypothesize that Electrode may actually be a form of energy instead of having an actual body.

data.name: Dark Flareon
data.flavorText: A Pokémon with a hot temper that can't be controlled once it's angered. Capable of breathing flames hotter than 3000°.

data.name: Dark Gloom
data.flavorText: Its pollen has such a strong smell that it even confuses itself at times.

data.name: Dark Golduck
data.flavorText: When Psyducks evolve, their headaches disappear and they find themselves in possession of formidable mental powers.

data.name: Dark Jolteon
data.flavorText: A dangerous Pokémon when angered. It likes to playfully shock people with the electricity it stores within its body.

data.name: Dark Kadabra
data.flavorText: Some people say that Kadabras are responsible for many of the mysterious events reported in the news.

data.name: Dark Machoke
data.flavorText: While normally peaceful and friendly, the number of incidents involving cruel Machokes is rising.

data.name: Dark Muk
data.flavorText: Muks appear suddenly, spreading sludge everywhere. Whenever one appears in a city, panic ensues.

data.name: Dark Persian
data.flavorText: Popular with women because of its beautiful fur. The leader of the Rockets keeps one as a pet.

data.name: Dark Primeape
data.flavorText: Although Primeapes have always been mean, lately they seem to be becoming even more vicious and frenzied.

data.name: Dark Rapidash
data.flavorText: A wild, uncontrollable Pokémon. When running, it looks like a comet streaking through the sky.

data.name: Dark Vaporeon
data.flavorText: A Pokémon capable of controlling water, so it is capable of creating giant whirlpools.

data.name: Dark Wartortle
data.flavorText: A Pokémon with a negative attitude, it hides in its shell whenever it's in a bad mood—which is often.

data.name: Magikarp
data.flavorText: Recent research has revealed the presence of dragon DNA in this species of Pokémon.

data.name: Porygon
data.flavorText: More and more people play the slots every day, trying to win a Porygon.

data.name: Abra
data.flavorText: It teleports itself away from danger, making it difficult to capture.

data.name: Charmander
data.flavorText: Many people find it cute and try to hold it, only to be burned by its tail.

data.name: Dark Raticate
data.flavorText: A Raticate's front teeth are incredibly powerful; it can destroy a two-story house with them in 5 minutes.

data.name: Diglett
data.flavorText: It follows Onixes in their tunnels, looking for scraps of food they have left behind.

data.name: Dratini
data.flavorText: The capture of the first Dratini inspired the search for other legendary Pokémon.

data.name: Drowzee
data.flavorText: Not popular with girls because of its attitude. Can often be heard muttering to itself in a low voice.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: A rare and unique Pokémon about which little is known, as few have been captured.

data.name: Ekans
data.flavorText: A carnivore that swallows its prey whole. Pidgeys and Spearows are its favorite food.

data.name: Grimer
data.flavorText: It has recently been found that Grimers are formed in waste-processing plants, and can move into towns via sewers.

data.name: Koffing
data.flavorText: First discovered in a weapons factory, this Pokémon can now be found almost anywhere.

data.name: Machop
data.flavorText: It's said that not even pro wrestlers can take down a Machop.

data.name: Magnemite
data.flavorText: It is said that enough Magnemites and Magnetons gather in one place, they can create a powerful magnetic barrier.

data.name: Mankey
data.flavorText: Normally friendly, it quickly becomes angry if it doesn't get what it wants.

data.name: Meowth
data.flavorText: A popular Pokémon that earns money for its owner with its "Pay Day" ability.

data.name: Oddish
data.flavorText: It wanders around at night sowing its seeds to create more Oddishes.

data.name: Ponyta
data.flavorText: A gentle grass-eater, it will allow riders on its back. However, anyone attempting to do so must be careful not to get burned.

data.name: Psyduck
data.flavorText: It is often seen holding its head in its paws, as if it were suffering from a headache.

data.name: Rattata
data.flavorText: Loves to eat walnuts, chestnuts, cheese, and milk.

data.name: Slowpoke
data.flavorText: Although it knows how to fish, no other intelligent behavior has been detected in it.

data.name: Squirtle
data.flavorText: Cute Pokémon that charms people with its innocent eyes. Loves swimming all day long.

data.name: Voltorb
data.flavorText: Usually seen only in power plants, it is sometimes seen in towns, apparently using the power lines to travel.

data.name: Zubat
data.flavorText: Lives in dark caves. Can occasionally be seen at night, when it flies in search of food.

data.name: Dark Raichu
data.flavorText: Stores up electricity in its body, then suddenly releases it to surprise and shock everyone.
